a em busca de um novo destino."	"bacia hidrográfica da baía de Guanabara;recuperação paisagística;região metropolitana do Rio de Janeiro"	"Guanabara Bay was, is and will remain the inflection for cariocas and fluminenses daily life, for better or
worse of Rio de Janeiro?s metropolitan region. For more than 40 years the studied bay has been a thriving
theme for the state's ecological actions, obtaining relative advances in the social, legal and economic
spheres. Meanwhile, when we approach the lens, several negative environmental patterns are identified,
very common to the environmental conditions of large metropolitan areas, without an effective
management and monitoring on the metropolis expansion, which exerts harsh pressure on its biophysical
environment. Amid this violent urban evolution, the beauty of its basin remains a haven for utopia, tuning
fork the metropolis lost harmony, where its thinning lies not only in the remediation of its water mirror, but
also of its mangroves, marshes, mountain ranges, cities composed of its minerals, all waiting for an
integrated driving. The result of this look is the proposal to unveil to society the benefits and harms of
metropolitan growth along the shores of the Guanabara Bay ecosystems. This study explores the
incongruities of actions, discourses, projects throughout the process of its bay estuary domination, the
way the metropolis shaped and framed natural landscapes with great emotional appealing and of identity.
The scope resides in this sine wave, as Guanabara?s life, in its urban landscape recovering to Rio de
Janeiro, in the up and down of the artificial nature, between valleys and peaks, where the waters sprout
and head forward to the sea. The essay about the title concept of this work is carried out at the boundaries
of neighborhoods where the first ecological aggressions of the metropolis began, cut by effluents and
